  "IMPORTANT NOTES SO READ IT PLEASE": {
    "First Note": "The members will be set automatically after the user accepts the invite. Once the invite is accepted, the user and role will be added to the members array in the format: { user: userId, role: roleId }",
    "Second Note": "When you create a new project for yourself, an Owner role will be automatically assigned to you. However, when you send an invite to someone, you must assign a role to the invited user. If you don't, the user will receive the Owner role by default — so don't forget to specify a role.",
    "Third Note": "If you assign the Admin permission to a role when creating it, all other permissions will be automatically included as well.",
    "Fourth Note": "The status field in a task is set to Pending by default when the task is created. You don't need to include it in the request body unless you're updating the task (e.g., via the update task API for drag-and-drop functionality)"
  },
